---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import config from '../data/config.json';

const { links } = config;
---

<Layout title="Call for Abstracts">
	<section class="page-header">
        <div class="container">
            <h1>Call for Abstracts</h1>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="content">
        <div class="container">

            <h2>Submission Guidelines</h2>
            <p>
                We invite researchers and practitioners to submit abstracts for consideration 
                in the Metaphorum 2026 program. Submissions should present original research, 
                theoretical reflections, methodological innovations, or compelling case studies 
                relevant to the conference streams below.
            </p>

            <div class="accordion">

                <!-- STREAM 1 -->
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <button class="accordion-header">1. Stafford Beer: a Genuinely Holistic Character</button>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <p>
                        Stafford Beer was not only a pioneering theorist, but also a mentor, artist, 
                        and humanist committed to designing systems that serve human dignity and planetary wellbeing...
                        </p>
                        <p>
                        This stream invites personal reflections and creative contributions that explore Beer in his 
                        wholeness and illuminate how he contributed to changing your way of thinking about organisations and societies.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- STREAM 2 -->
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <button class="accordion-header">2. Constitutive Principles, Emerging Methods and Tools, and Contemporary Practice</button>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <p>
                        At the heart of organisational cybernetics lie the Viable System Model and Team Syntegrity...
                        </p>

                        <ul>
                            <li>What are the constitutive principles of organisational viability?</li>
                            <li>What are emerging and proven methodologies and tools?</li>
                            <li>What forms of learning have emerged through practical application?</li>
                            <li>What are the main challenges for further development?</li>
                        </ul>

                        <p>
                        We invite theoretical and methodological innovations, case studies, and critical reflections.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- STREAM 3 -->
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <button class="accordion-header">3. Beyond Beer: Toward Resilient, Just, and Ethical Viable Systems</button>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <p>
                        As humanity faces climate disruption, biodiversity loss, rising inequality, 
                        and political unrest, the need for resilience, justice, and sustainability 
                        has never been more urgent.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                        This stream invites contributions that extend or reinterpret cybernetic 
                        principles to address emerging socio-ecological challenges.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- STREAM 4 -->
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <button class="accordion-header">4. Beyond Beer: Living or Grounded Cybernetics</button>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <p>
                        Inspired by Metaphorum’s idea of ‘Barefoot Cybernetics’, this stream 
                        views organisational cybernetics as an emancipatory approach.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                        We welcome interdisciplinary perspectives, empirical contributions, 
                        and action-oriented frameworks that advance structural transformation.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <!-- STREAM 5 -->
                <div class="accordion-item">
                    <button class="accordion-header">5. The World in Torment: A Time Whose Ideas Must Come</button>
                    <div class="accordion-content">
                        <p>
                        In January 1993, Stafford Beer delivered his Presidential Address 
                        titled “The World in Torment: A Time Whose Ideas Must Come”.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                        This panel explores current global systemic failures, institutional 
                        obsolescence, and complexity challenges in governance.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                        Since 1993, digital networks and artificial intelligence have reshaped 
                        global systems — raising new questions of control, responsibility, and systemic design.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>

            </div>

            <!-- ALWAYS VISIBLE SECTION -->
            <div class="methodology">
                <h2>Methodological Approach: A Living Conversation</h2>
                <p>
                These streams form a single, integrated conversation. Personal reflections illuminate 
                the ethical foundations of the field; practice tests and refines its principles; and 
                future-oriented inquiry ensures continued relevance.
                </p>
                <p>
                We welcome creative workshops, interdisciplinary panels, posters, traditional papers, 
                and other facilitated group dynamics.
                </p>
                <p>
                Those interested in publishing may participate in a special issue of:
                <br />
                <strong>Systemic Practice and Action Research</strong> and/or 
                <strong>Systems Research and Behavioural Science</strong> and/or 
                <strong>A New Metaphorum Online Journal (Organisational Systems)</strong>
                </p>

                <p class="deadline">
                    <strong>Deadline for submitting abstracts:</strong> May 30th, 2026
                </p>

                <p>
                    Email submissions to 
                    <a href={`mailto:${links.abstracts_email}`}>
                        {links.abstracts_email}
                    </a>
                </p>
            </div>

        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>

<script>
    document.querySelectorAll('.accordion-header').forEach(button => {
        button.addEventListener('click', () => {
            const content = button.nextElementSibling;
            content.classList.toggle('open');
        });
    });
</script>

<style>
.page-header {
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: white;
    padding: 3rem 0;
}

.accordion-item {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    overflow: hidden;
}

.accordion-header {
    width: 100%;
    text-align: left;
    padding: 1rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    background: var(--color-background-alt);
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
}

.accordion-content {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.4s ease;
    padding: 0 1rem;
}

.accordion-content.open {
    max-height: 1000px;
    padding: 1rem;
}

.methodology {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: var(--color-background-alt);
    border-radius: 8px;
}

.deadline {
    margin-top: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
}
</style>